is: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 6 suffering_focused → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJzFWWtv2zoS%2FSuDosXaaWTLzjtFPuThtEXT3myS297dpnBpibZ5LYkqSUVxe9PfvoeU5FfsJN27wAYIqkri8MzwzMwZ5cezkPdZFpljGfJn%2B8%2BaTTo4OKArxURCRlKg2PcxLvKErrO239qkXKoovBE8p7zVbXc3ulvd7e5Od5dq2siUduvWwHUCQ4daZ3FqhEwoGMLePvmUMiWDoWCRNdfaa1OL%2Bkx1Wc7G3WEWs0RXD9rEEhGzSHe1jHk%2BZKZ6skH9zGSKlwu6MTOGq24uzLAbCh3ILDEiGVSvb00MlS%2BybiQnxrZJZ%2F0%2BV1jQ7csg0zysHu1QzJnp4heLUiV7EY%2BrZ7uUcNNN%2BIAZccO7xQ7dCNfa%2Bd5hwZDYNABCE6PzsRniui8iTgjv9LFukrEOsjDU66Q4zkQkXJNUzpjiHuLGYg4gQuO%2BGfIipP%2FQiEUSOBuvKJBxKrV1ffIC1iYhh0XcEgU0bVgSskgmnGIcetSgr5Mz7dx8tVDtcn6b8sBg4Q2LMk6y7yxMj7%2FhjB1xbaiXjSmz29iFms86tk%2BXQyXilD7xCAfN6VzJP2G3WP2686FzcXjVOaHemAY84QqxbqTjims8FGYuTGt4uE4Jjs%2BBsZGEJWfr9yTgyliXY6nAr0nEdPFuEQ6WppHgukGX47gRyUEiFQ6u9iPdWqd0b%2Buu7my509rzX9Dx21fuzR43rLhrecB6IhIGQHrSuh3aRPnsr1PrS4NOWWAk9oSvhSm8kNozSMw6aUncEkOqAU6u8zk%2FOTz7V%2FP5F%2BrxSObIBLvWnTC%2FxXU0xnLYRlSdLewdZoEpzoJbdiYa7vcjmWHVEAd%2FUtKfDu47iPRr%2BLvOTXu5e1cncuSCTfiQczEYwjaSVYHylkVDRMvyUFPtSsZMi9Er%2BgiH7LO23%2FYRrEnynCsB6Ga8fOdWo1VuvN3YKjfmt0axmW3ZDc7PmobPPAGNJrZXb18Ugoe93uDexG17vV3un2KlZ0TM6SUFzDBtlEwRVlskkoy5tLXZy