e Project&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Benatar)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem → 8 net_negative_animal_lives" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJzFWGtT28gS%2FStdVFLXJsiWDYRHig88TJIKyXKB3ey9IeWMpbE9a0mjzIwQTpb97ffMSPILG5xPlyoKIc10n%2B4%2B%2FZj5uRHyPssicypDvnG40WzS0dER3SgmEjKSAsV%2BjPGQJ3Sbtf3WDuVSReGd4DnlrW67u93d7e5196mmjUxpv2633yYQc6x1FqdGyISCIaQdkk8pUzIYChZZYa2DNrWoz1SX5WzcHWYxS3T1oU0sETGLdFfLmOdDZqov29TPTKZ4uaEbM2O46ubCDLuh0IHMEiOSQbV8dyKoXMi6kZwI26OYM9PFL76kSvYiHlff9inhppvwATPijncLMd0Iz9oZ2GHBkNjUSqGJ0eXYDPHcFxEneHD6WTfJWCtYGOotUhxuFwnXJJUTprgH57CYA4jQeG%2BGvPDbvzQMTgIn4w0FMk6ltvZNFmBvEnJIxCtRQNOGJSGLZMIpRlyjBn2bhK1z981Ctdv5fcoDg413LMo4yb6TMI1wwwk74dpQLxtTZtXYjZrPGnZI10Ml4pQ%2B8wjR5HSp5F%2BQW%2Bx%2B2%2FnUuTq%2B6ZxRb0wDnnAFXzfScUUnHgoz56ZNfNyiBDFyYKwnIcnJ%2Bj0JuDLW5FgqkGjiMV2sLdzB0jQSXDfoehw3IjlIpELgaj%2FT3S1KD3Yf6k6Wi9aB%2F5JO379xK3vcsOKt5QHriUgYAOlJa3Zoc%2BGLv0Wtrw06Z4GR0AlbC1FYkNoYJGaLtCRuiSHVAJHrfMnPji%2F%2B03zxlXo8kjnobve6C